      "body" : "@paraboul Multi-wallet is planned, but I'm not sure it's really something targetting your use case. There should be no reason to isolate coins per-user. That just creates higher transaction fees for your users, prevents you from implementing proper security (an offline wallet), and propagates harmful myths about Bitcoin (such as that transactions have \"from\" or \"return\" addresses).\r\n\r\nWhat real problem are you trying to solve here, that you think needs each user to have isolated coins?",
